org.apache.flink.runtime.jobgraph.tasks

类 AbstractInvokable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.jobgraph.tasks.AbstractInvokable
  • 直接已知子类:
    BatchTask, DataSinkTask, DataSourceTask, IterationSynchronizationSinkTask, StreamTask

    public abstract class AbstractInvokable
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the abstract base class for every task that can be executed by a TaskManager. Concrete tasks like the vertices of batch jobs (see BatchTask inherit from this class.

    The TaskManager invokes the invoke() method when executing a task. All operations of the task happen in this method (setting up input output stream readers and writers as well as the task's core operation).

      • invoke

        public abstract void invoke()
                     throws java.lang.Exception
        Starts the execution.

        Must be overwritten by the concrete task implementation. This method is called by the task manager when the actual execution of the task starts.

        All resources should be cleaned up when the method returns. Make sure to guard the code with try-finally blocks where necessary.

        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - Tasks may forward their exceptions for the TaskManager to handle through failure/recovery.

      • cancel

        public void cancel()
            throws java.lang.Exception
        This method is called when a task is canceled either as a result of a user abort or an execution failure. It can be overwritten to respond to shut down the user code properly.
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - thrown if any exception occurs during the execution of the user code
